					  ADGA Season Kicks Off This Saturday  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  May 3, 2011    1 Comment  

					 

 A big field is shaping up for the Akron District Golf Associations 2011 inaugural event, the  Parke H. Thornton Two-Man Better Ball  at Turkeyfoot Lake Golf Links in Akron this Saturday, May 7th.  
 A whopping 45 teams are already registered and entries close Wednesday at 10 p.m. To sign up, visit the  ADGA website . 

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  Tee It Up with the ADGA in 2011!  

					 by Tim Davis  |  March 1, 2011    No Comments  

					 

 The Akron District Golf Association (ADGA), in its quest for the betterment of amateur golf in the greater Akron community, continues to refine its tournament schedule, formats, and payouts to provide its members with the best competition in the Akron area.  
 We hope golfers from all over Northeast Ohio will join us in 2011 in the events of the ADGA!  [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  Mike Simpson Wins ADGA Golfer of the Year Tournament; Fred Miller Nabs Seniors  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  October 4, 2010    No Comments  

					 

    Champion Mike Simpson hits his final tee shot at the ADGA Golfer of the Year tournament.  
 In truly challenging weather conditions this weekend, Mike Simpson earned a one shot victory in the Akron District Golf Association’s Golfer of the Year Tournament at the West and North Courses at Firestone Country Club in Akron. 
 And with that victory, Simpson also won the ADGA’s 2010 Player of the Year honors.   [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

