 The field has been set for the Akron District Golf Association’s 2010 Golfer of the Year tournament, to be played on Saturday, October 2nd at Firestone Country Club’s West Course and on Sunday, October 3rd at the North Course. 
 Invitations have been extended to the 48 eligible players: the top 24 points earners of the ADGA’s 2010 season from both the main division and senior division:   [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  Simpson & Oates, Marr & Trier Top ADGA Lazor 2-M  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  July 11, 2010    No Comments  

					 

  Dan Marr holes this 16-foot birdie putt on 18 to earn a share of the 2010 ADGA Lazor 2-Man  
  The teams of Mike Simpson & Dave Oates and Dave Trier & Dan Marr shared top honors in the 2010 ADGA Lazor 2-Man better ball event at Chippewa Golf Club on Saturday. 
 Each team shot a 6-under par 65, two shots better than the three teams who tied for third at 67.   [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  Lambos Captures ADGA 36-Hole Stroke Play  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  June 27, 2010    No Comments  

					 

 Nick Lambos of Canton didn’t back off his first round lead. 
 Lambos put together a solid round of even par 72 on Sunday at the challenging Seven Hills Country Club in Hartville to win the 2010 ADGA Lanning’s 36-Hole Stroke Play Tournament by one shot over Aaron Crewes of Uniontown.   [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  Lambos, Beal Lead ADGA 36-Holer  

					 by Tim Davis  |  June 26, 2010    No Comments  

					 

 Nick Lambos and defending champion Ross Beal lead the pack after tying with a score of 69 after round one of the 2010 ADGA Lannings Restaurant 36-hole stroke play event. 
 But a huge number of players are right on their heels, including 11 players who are within five shots of the lead going into day two at Seven Hills CC on Sunday.   [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

				 

			

				
 
